stylometry: Data mining is just as it sounds we are mining for data.  When we have a cluster of a group of stats for example we can use this data mining to search for certain things within that data.  This can be very usefull to a company in that they may have a long list of costumers and they want to find out for example, which ones live in ohio, as well as shop on their site grater than 2 times a week.  From there we can cluster all these people into groups such as their age.  If we have the information we can cluster the data into groups through the data mining.  Searching or "mining" through the data to find similarities or the differences between the data to help your company make a good business decision.
